Python time module
time.sleep(time in s/m/h)   -
1. But using this will make the performance of the script poor.
2. Even after the wait and if still element is not available then it will still throw exception

Wait Commands:

1. implicit wait -
pros:
Single Statement
performance is not reduced. Its applicable to all the elements in the script.

cons:
Even after the wait and if still element is not available then it will still throw exception


2. explicit wait - It works based on the condition
pros: works more effectively.
cons: some difficulty as we need to add every where when synchronization issue occurs.

